Principles of compiling research in the field of Educational Science. Requirements of scientific research. Ethical requirements of scientific research. Principles and possibilities of planning scientific research. Choosing the topic and its relevance to preschool education. Possibilities of searching information, sources and databases related to preschool education. Work with theoretical materials. Defining a research problem. Data collection and an analysis in qualitative and quantitative research design. Presentation of research results. Requirements of compilation and formalisation of the research.Objectives/eesmärkid:  A broad orientation in the principles of scientific research, planning and developing primary skills of performing the research.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  As a result of passing the subject, the student: Is able to analyze the reality of education in Estonia and to find out the topics of pre-school education that need to be researched; Is familiar with the basic concepts of scientific research and knows the methodology of scientific research; Is able to plan empirical research required for undergraduate work.
